<section id="biography">
  <h1>Biography</h1>

  <h2>Early years and emergence (2015–2017)</h2>
  <p> Gurli Octavia began releasing music in the late-2010s, initially gaining attention through live performances and early demo releases on SoundCloud, gaining thousand of streams on her bedroom demos. Between 2017 and 2019, she released three conceptually linked EPs - _Philophobia_, _Lunacy_ (LACOBR), and _Metanoia_ (Sony) - establishing her as a distinctive voice in the Danish independent music scene. The releases were accompanied by extensive live activity and growing radio support. <p> 

  <h2>EP trilogy and growing live activity (2017–2019)</h2>
  <p>From 2017 to 2019 she released a three-part EP sequence: <em>Philophobia</em>, <em>Lunacy</em>, and <em>Metanoia</em>. The releases established a consistent solo catalogue and were accompanied by ongoing concert activity, including showcase and festival appearances in Denmark.</p>

  <h2>Debut album (2021)</h2>
  <p>In 2021 she released her debut full-length album <em>I Could Be Blossoming Instead</em>, expanding her scope in production and format and anchoring a new phase of releases and performance work.</p>

  <h2>Recent work and parallel activity (2022–present)</h2>
  <p>Following the album cycle, she continued releasing singles and developing live work while expanding her practice into international sessions and a parallel project under a separate moniker.</p>

  <h2>Education</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>MA, Creative Music Production, ICMP London (2025)</li>
    <li>BA, Songwriting, The Royal Academy of Music Aarhus/Aalborg (Det Jyske Musikkonservatorium) (2020)</li>
  </ul>
</section>
